<br>
This is a grave mistake you are making.  You are essentially assuming here that if you mind your own business and leave everyone else alone that they will reciprocate.<br>
<br>
It doesn't work that way.<br>
<br>
Take a look at history.  Poland, Czechoslovakia, Russia, Austria, and many other nations were minding their own business in WW2.  The same can be said in WW1.  The countries conquered by the Soviet Union were minding their own business for the most part.  Many wars have started unprovoked, for the simple reason that more powerful nations saw an opportunity to conquer less powerful nations and profit from it financially, territorially, militarily, or otherwise.  Just because no nation has a vendetta against you doesn't mean that you are safe.<br>
<br>
As far as the appeasement of terrorists, it would probably work in the sense that they'd leave us alone.  However, it would not be the morally correct thing to do.  It would leave many innocent people to be victims of terror around the world, people far less capable of defending themselves.  You would leave the rest of the world to die, and hide away in your own little corner until you were the last ones left, and eventually, they'd come for you too.<br>
<br>
