<br>
Whether or not the world is a better place due to our constant assertion into other countries' affairs is up for debate, and not at all relevant to my above statement.<br>
<br>
However if we had not gotten involved in this area at all, and again I'm not condemning or condoning it, then we wouldn't be a desired target for terrorists.  Sure, maybe other terrorists would be attacking us for different reasons.  Maybe the world would be in turmoil right now.  I'm not trying to guess what may have happened if we didn't have such an active foreign presence, but what is done to us is a result of our country's decision to act to what we see as the benefit of other countries.<br>
<br>
So while no country deserves the mass-murdering of 3,000 of their people, that's not to say that the country did not bring it upon themselves.  <br>
