<br>
Two words, very similar, yet very different. America, the country, provoked an act of war. Americans, the people, largely had nothing to do with it, and should have been left out of it. One of the rules of war is that you don't attack civilian targets. It's the rule that AQ broke, and the reason that the attack in question was an atrocity. I doubt very much that we'd be having this conversation if they'd attacked a military target instead of the WTC. Except that they've been attacking military targets for a decade or more....<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Doing the right thing can have bad consequences.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And therein lies the debate. I don't believe that you've been doing the right thing. I believe that you've been intervening and practicing colonial and imperial maneuvers since the early 20th century. I believe that you've been sticking your nose where it doesn't belong. And I believe that it's finally come back to bite you in the ass.  I believe that an attack on the US was inevitable. And I am surprised that it took as long as it did.<br>
<br>
In short, while I abhor their methods, I understand their reasons. The world would be great if we could solve our differences diplomatically.<br>
<br>
Prove to me that you've been doing the right thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
But that's all beside the point. Hindsight is all well and good, but now you have to deal with the present. We can't go back in time to fix past mistakes, we can only work with what we've got now. As far as I can tell, you haven't been doing the right thing, but I don't think it's too late to fix the course you're on. So like I said, in a different world you wouldn't have to spend as much on defense as you do. But now, you don't really have a choice. But that doesn't mean that you can't work towards a world where you don't need as much in the future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1458<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/16/03 5:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wow that's a big ass deficit</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I believe that you've been intervening and practicing colonial and imperial maneuvers since the early 20th century.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
